### TABLEDATA

CREATE TABLE quantum_computing_jobs (
    job_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    job_name VARCHAR(255),
    submission_time TIMESTAMP,
    execution_time TIMESTAMP,
    status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_computing_results (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    job_id UUID,
    result_data JSON,
    result_time TIMESTAMP,
    execution_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_computing_users (
    user_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE quantum_computing_logs (
    log_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    log_time TIMESTAMP,
    message TEXT
);
